column4: im wondering if theres something on my motherboard that would make it reject non-emachines PSUs since my computer is a pre-built emachines
lol thats why i bought it
you mean a fan connected to the MB?
no i dont think the PSU has its fan conencted directly to the MB though
yes the motherboard has its 4 pin connected to the PSU as well
no i am not getting nopower whatsoever even the case fan do not start
no the MB isn't dead because I'm using it right now with the older PSU
I work at a computer repair place.. there isn't anything like that on an emachines
you're not getting anything or just no video? have you made sure you've got the 4-pin connector plugged in too if the mobo has a slot for it?
other than that.. maybe it was really the mobo that went out
exchange it for a good one
it's a dead PSU if it makes sound for a second then nothing until you unplug it for a bit
I bet the caps are bad
